# Product Business Modeling Rule

Business Modeling is an Agent-neutral Core. Cursor rules are runtime guidance only.

Use these project asset roots:

```text
docs/product/business-modeling/
docs/product/model-triggers/
docs/product/work-items/
```

Follow the Core contract:

- business attributes are not database fields;
- `schema-view.json` only contains business objects, business domains, object categories, business attributes, and example content;
- high-impact semantics require human confirmation before `confirmed`;
- passive trigger response writes `MODEL_IMPACT_REPORT.md`;
- downstream views are derived views, not source of truth;
- do not directly edit `docs/design/**`, Reference Library, or Color Card Registry from Business Modeling.

When a user asks for business modeling work, follow the Product Business Modeling workflow and create or resume a BM Work Item when the task has persistent modeling value.
